Join us here for a PREVIEW of our daily one-hour RUMBLE show. 
To continue watching the show in full, join me exclusively over on RUMBLE: https://bit.ly/SF524-live

Today's show covers Elon Musk’s controversial inauguration moments, the media’s obsession with symbolic gestures, and the deeper implications of Trump’s executive orders and Biden’s preemptive pardons. We dive into the World Health Organization’s funding, vaccine politics, and the connections between Fauci and past administrations. There’s also a critical look at the Southport murders, media narratives, and the cultural decay that allows institutional failures. Finally, we reflect on the intersection of religion and politics, exploring the symbolic and spiritual roles they play in shaping society.
title: Inside Trump’s Inauguration: Media Frenzy, Pardons, and Power Plays – SF524
